wikipedia_page.main: Jabez Foster (born 15 September 1902) was an English professional footballer of the 1920s. Born in Darlaston, he joined Gillingham from Bristol Rovers in 1926 and went on to make 21 appearances for the club in The Football League. He left to join Wellington Town in 1927.

response: Michael Jabez Foster (born 26 February 1946) is a British lawyer and Labour politician who served as the Member of Parliament (MP) for Hastings and Rye from 1997 to 2010, and served in government as a Minister for Equalities from 2009 to 2010.
